Gazprom Merges Foreign Exploration Units to Expand Abroad

-- B y   A n n a   S h i r y a e v s k a y a
-- 
2011-05-23T11:39:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/gazprom-merges-foreign-exploration-units-to-expand-abroad.html
OAO Gazprom is merging its
international exploration and production units to simplify
financing and streamline decision-making as the Russian gas
monopoly expands overseas.  Gazprom EP International BV , its Amsterdam-based unit with
projects in North Africa and  South America , will take over ZAO
Gazprom Zarubezhneftegaz, which mainly develops assets in the
former Soviet Union and Vietnam, by the middle of 2012,
according to a statement today.  Gazprom plans to expand into Bangladesh, Uruguay,  Sri
Lanka , Pakistan, Namibia and Nigeria among others.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anna Shiryaevskaya in Moscow at 
 ashiryaevska@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Kennedy at   wkennedy3@bloomberg.net  